## Summary

The piece argued that better frontend output comes from giving the model a strong design frame: composition rules, mood references, content structure, and explicit constraints about typography, hero layout, color, and motion. The interesting subtext is that frontier models still regress toward generic, high-frequency UI patterns when prompts stay vague.

