30_knowledge/capture/delightful-frontends-with-gpt.md | The piece argued that better frontend output comes from giving the model a strong design frame: composition rules, mood references, content structure, and explicit constraints about typography, hero layout, color, and motion. The interesting subtext is that frontier models still regress toward generic, high-frequency UI patterns when prompts stay vague.
30_knowledge/capture/delightful-frontends-with-gpt.md | That makes this article useful beyond frontend work. It is another example of a broader pattern in agent design: quality improves when the operator specifies taste, constraints, and verification surfaces early rather than hoping the model will infer them from a short ask.
30_knowledge/capture/delightful-frontends-with-gpt.md | - The guide recommends starting with design principles, not components.
30_knowledge/capture/delightful-frontends-with-gpt.md | - Playwright-style verification is framed as part of the design loop, not just as a testing afterthought.
30_knowledge/capture/mcp-market-gap-is-trust.md | That framing is helpful because it shifts attention from wrapper proliferation toward curation, verification, managed hosting, and workflow design. In other words: the market gap may be downstream of protocol adoption, not upstream of it.
30_knowledge/capture/nemoclaw-overview.md | - **Why keep this:** a compact overview of an “agent runtime as reference stack” design that bundles sandboxing, inference routing, and lifecycle management.
30_knowledge/capture/nemoclaw-overview.md | - The system is explicitly designed for always-on assistants, which makes lifecycle and hot-reloadable policy central.
30_knowledge/notes/design-constraints-for-a-household-assistant.md | This system is being designed for a life made of fragments.
30_knowledge/notes/why-i-keep-coming-back-to-a-personal-assistant.md | - the hard part is reducing friction without turning life into an overdesigned cockpit
30_knowledge/notes/why-i-keep-coming-back-to-a-personal-assistant.md | Part of the reason I care so much is that I am also designing for the version of myself I actually have, not the heroic founder version from startup mythology.
